LAGOS â€“ Former President Olusegun Obasanjo has charged Nigerian youths to emulate the sterling qualities in General Aguiyi Ironsi, former the head of state and commander- in-chief of the Armed Forces, and Dr. Michael Okpara, the premier of the Eastern Region from 1960 to 1966. He made the remarks when he paid condolence visits to the homes of the departed national icons. Obasanjo, who was in company of the members of Ohanaeze Ndigbo Worldwide started with the home of General Ironsi whose wife, Mrs Victoria Aguiyi Ironsi was buried on November 6 2021. APC: Members Plan Heroic Welcome For CECPC Buni IWD: SWAN Urges NASS To Revisit Gender Bills The son of Ironsi, Ambassador Thomas Ironsi, and his family members were on ground at the Ironsi country home in Ibeku, Umuahia, to receive Obasanjo and his entourage. Obasanjo, in his condolence message, regretted his absence during the burial of Mrs Ironsi. Obasanjo recalled his relationship with Ironsi and his early years in the Armed Forces He revealed how some Igbo army officers especially Ironsi, Col. Njoku and a few others influenced his military actions most positively. He narrated the glorious years when the image of Nigeria towered so high in the comity of nations, stating that for a Nigerian to command the peace keeping force in Congo was a function of the confidence the global community reposed in Nigeria of yore. He urged the Ironsi offspring and Nigerian youths to emulate the virtues in Ironsi. Ambassador Ironsi, who was appointed an Ambassador and later the Minister of Defence under Obasanjo, expressed profound gratitude to Obasanjo and his entourage